article.linkText: Northern Iowa earns 78-73 win over Richmond
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- — Trey Campbell's 21 points helped Northern Iowa defeat Richmond 78-73 on Wednesday night. Campbell was 7 of 12 shooting (6 for 9 from 3-point range) for the Panthers (3-6). Bowen Born scored 17 points, going 5 of 14 from the floor, including 2 for 7 from 3-point range, and 5 for 5 from the line. Nate Heise shot 5 for 9 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 1 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 13 points. The Spiders (5-4) were led by Jordan King, who recorded 20 points. Richmond also got 17 points and six rebounds from Isaiah Bigelow. Neal Quinn also had 11 points and eight rebounds. Northern Iowa visits Toledo and Richmond travels to Florida, both games on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
